:::{{DIcon|Talk}} About the history of the Express...
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_100050706-->
::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 himeko 119.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' The Astral Express was a tool created by Akivili the Trailblaze, who used it to transport THEMSELF and the Nameless across the galaxy. It is rumored that there are other vehicles like it, but the Express has no such records.
::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 himeko 120.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' When I found the Express, its memory had been severely damaged, with much of its valuable information lost. All I know is that the Express is an Aspect of Creation built by Akivili themself, and used to travel the cosmos.
::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 himeko 121.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' As for how it was built and how it was damaged, I do not have an answer.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Talk}} About where the Express is headed...
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_100050710-->
::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 himeko 122.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' The Express is traveling on a route that the Trailblaze once embarked on. The names of some destinations have been lost, but the first and final stops were both at Pegana &mdash; Akivili's home world.
::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 himeko 123.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' We speculate the Astral Express started its journey from Pegana, stopping at each destination along the way before returning there for its next journey. However, the appearance of the Stellarons has caused a delay at each stop.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Talk}} About the Express' source of power...
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_100050713-->
::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 himeko 124.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' There is a legend in the galaxy: The heart of Akivili themself lies in the core of the Astral Express, providing it with the power to travel between worlds. But I found no evidence of that aboard the Express.
::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 himeko 125.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' Besides, the Express existed before the Trailblaze fell. There's no way they could have had two hearts, right? However, it is likely that the Express possesses some sort of mechanism to transfer power from the Trailblaze.
::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 himeko 126.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' It wouldn't be possible with a normal Pathstrider.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Talk}} About Akivili...
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_100050717-->
::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 himeko 127.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' The fallen Aeon, deceased Trailblaze &mdash; THEIR passing is still a mystery, but of all the known Aeons, Akivili was the closest to mankind.
::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 himeko 128.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' In the databank aboard the Express, it is recorded that THEY walked among the mortals &mdash; adventuring, fighting, and celebrating with THEM. Although THEY were an Aeon restrained by the "Primum Mobile," Akivili enjoyed a freedom similar to us mortals.
::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 himeko 129.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' THEY were different from most... But THEIR passing came so suddenly that it was thought THEY were killed by another Aeon. I don't believe that to be the case.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Return}} I have another question...
::::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_100050306_10-->
:::;(<!--Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString)-->)
::::{{DIcon|Talk}} About the galaxy...
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_100050722-->
:::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 himeko 130.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' The galaxy is endlessly vast. I wouldn't know where to begin, especially if you ask me that so suddenly...
:::::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_100050306_33-->
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_100050306_33-->
:::::{{DIcon|Talk}} About its nature...
::::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_100050724-->
::::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 himeko 131.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' I've been to many different worlds, yet I still know very little about the galaxy, simply because it's too vast. As for its nature, there are a few theories that I can share with you.
::::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 himeko 132.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' The most popular is probably the Cosmos Tree theory, proposed by Zandar, Emanator of Erudition and the first member of the Genius Society. He compared the galaxy to an enormous imaginary tree, with its leaves being individual universes.
::::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 himeko 133.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' Therefore, only Aeons, who draw their energy from the imaginary, and Emanators, who are blessed by Aeons, can travel through the spaces filled with imaginary energy. That's why planets where civilizations exist are so similar.
::::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 himeko 134.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' However, the theory has its flaws. Elias Salas, the 56th member of the Genius Society, invented remote detection, disproving that the imaginary is unique. This shook the foundation of the "Cosmos Tree" theory.
::::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 himeko 135.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' There are other theories as well: The "Stretching" theory, the "Heat Torch" theory, and the "Parallel Imaging" theory... The Riddlers claim the galaxy is just a dream and IX's followers seem to like that claim.
:::::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::::{{DIcon|Talk}} About the Aeons...
::::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_100050730-->
::::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 himeko 136.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' Aeons are the most mysterious beings in the galaxy. All we know is that THEY ascended from the form of intelligent beings. As for the how and why, even the geniuses over at the Genius Society haven't the slightest clue.
::::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 himeko 137.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' Upon ascending to Aeon-hood, that being gains power over the Paths, free to choose the allocation of imaginary energy however THEY wish, while suffering the restrictions of the "Primum Mobile."
::::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 himeko 138.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' The Aeon of Destruction seeks only to destroy the universe, while the Aeon of Erudition wants to find the answer for all that exists. Meanwhile, the Aeon of Preservation continues to forge walls, and the Aeon of Enigmata devotes themself to obscuring all that is known...
::::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 himeko 139.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' A cloud of mystery shrouds the Aeons. I heard Madam Herta recruited a team to try and solve the mysteries about THEM.
:::::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::::{{DIcon|Talk}} About the factions...
::::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_100050735-->
::::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 himeko 140.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' Compared to the Aeons, the factions are much easier to understand. Mortals with the same objective gather together to practice their understanding of Aeons and the Paths.
::::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 himeko 141.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' Many Aeons are unreachable, but the factions are close to us. After Akivili trailblazed across the galaxy, people became aware of the existence of other worlds. Gradually, more people started trying to use the power of the Aeons to travel between worlds.
::::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 himeko 142.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' The Interastral Peace Corporation is a good example: They worship Qlipoth, the Aeon of Preservation, but somehow became the largest economic entity in the galaxy;
::::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 himeko 143.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' Another example is the Genius Society: There is no shortage of eccentrics like Madam Herta who dedicate themselves to scientific research under the protection of the Erudition.
::::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 himeko 144.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' These factions possess the same power as us to voyage between worlds. It would be hard to travel through the galaxy without them.
:::::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::::{{DIcon|Talk}} About the Paths...
::::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_100050741-->
::::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 himeko 145.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' The birth of an Aeon gives rise to a Path. The nature of the Paths remains a mystery, leaving us to draw an analogy in a way that mortals can understand: It's a philosophical concept of sorts.
::::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 himeko 146.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' A person is considered to be on a Path when their will overlaps with that Path. If the person has a strong enough will, they can draw power from that Path. Those who can do so are called Pathstriders.
::::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 himeko 147.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' Pathstriders possess extraordinary power, but are still insignificant compared to the Aeons, like a drop of water in a vast ocean. Sometimes, Aeons will bestow a mortal with their power, making them an "Emanator" of that Aeon.
::::::{{A|VO chapter0 7 himeko 149.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' I should mention that once a Path is open, it cannot be closed, even with the fall of its Aeon. That is how we are still able to travel across the stars, despite Akivili's passing.
:::::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
