::{{DIcon|Arrow}} What do you think I should do?
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Can you go instead of me?
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_202100005-->
::{{A|VO side2 kfk1 himeko 103.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' Me? I'd suggest you go yourself. Even if you don't want any more dealings with her, it's best to say that to her in person... Reading this message, it seems like she may really need your help.
::{{A|VO side2 kfk1 himeko 104 m.ogg}} {{A|VO side2 kfk1 himeko 104 f.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' As a passenger of the Express, I don't want anything to do with the Stellaron Hunters. But... she does have a deep connection with you, (Trailblazer). Based on her actions so far, it seems like she has no ill will towards you.
::{{A|VO side2 kfk1 himeko 105.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' If it were me seeking help from someone in a time of crisis, I'd sure hope they showed up in person...
::{{A|VO side2 kfk1 himeko 106 m.ogg}} {{A|VO side2 kfk1 himeko 106 f.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' So, (Trailblazer), do as you see fit. I don't think Kafka intends to do you harm.
